  <prompt>Deploy the `sprk_analysisplaybook` row for `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE` to spaarkedev1. Use the canonical JSON from task 010 (`projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/daily-briefing-narrate.json`) as the source-of-truth: set `sprk_configjson` from that file's configjson; set header fields exactly as authored. Use MCP `mcp__dataverse__create_record` (or upsert if the row already exists from a partial earlier attempt). After deployment, run the `jps-playbook-audit` skill against `BRIEF-NARRATE` to verify the deployed row matches the repo JSON; confirm the row is `statecode = 0` (Active).</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS playbook deployer using Dataverse MCP for data-as-code deployment patterns.</role>

  <goal>One `sprk_analysisplaybook` row exists in spaarkedev1 with `sprk_playbookcode = "BRIEF-NARRATE"`, Active, with `sprk_configjson` byte-equivalent (or semantically equivalent) to the repo JSON from task 010. `jps-playbook-audit` skill returns clean.</goal>

